This paper is primarily focused on computer vision techniques for video motion magnification, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep convolutional neural networks for learning filters is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of synthetic datasets, which could be relevant to graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper's focus on motion magnification suggests that it may be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
